snippet.title: Biden projects confidence as Trump campaign threatens recount - 11/4 (FULL LIVE STREAM)
snippet.description:
There are still millions of votes left to be counted in the 2020 election, particularly in states like Michigan and Pennsylvania. The outstanding votes that will ultimately decide the presidency, Senate and House races are primarily in Democratic-leaning areas.

It is typical for ballots to be counted for days after election night. Close races often take days or weeks to settle. In most states, vote counts aren’t official until weeks after Election Day. But this year, the delays in counting have been amplified by unprecedented levels of mail-in voting. Read more: https://wapo.st/34VQuH6.
